The claim that E.G. White was an innovator was removed as it is unfounded. The main two things she is known for by non-Adventists are her prolific writing and being co-founder of the Seventh-day Adventist Church. As such, the latter was used to substitute the omitted opening claim. Ellen G. White herself ascribed her visions, inspiration, and spiritual insight to God. As such, in response to such a claim, she would have ascribed such a title to him.
